title: Jennie Lakip
data: Jennie Marshall Lakip (née Marshall; born September 15, 1990) is an American soccer player who plays as a striker for Querétaro. Lakip attended Brigham Young University in the United States, where she was regarded as one of the soccer team's most important players.[1] While playing for Costa Rican side Dimas Escazú, Lakip was the top scorer of the 2021 Costa Rican Women's Premier Division with fourteen goals.[2] After that, she played for Costa Rican side Alajuelense.[3] She was regarded as one of the club's most important players.[4] Lakip mainly operates as a striker and has been described as a "player with goals, control of the ball, a lot of technique and she also knows how to use her body very well".[5] Lakip married husband Romy Lakip in 2013, and has two children.[6][7] She has regarded Norway international Erling Haaland as her football idol.[8] This biographical article related to women's soccer in the United States is a stub.
